<doc id="164524" wikidata="Q16887532" url="?curid=164524" title="Jam sync">
<text>Jam sync refers to the practice of applying a phase hit to a system to bring it in synchronization with another. The term originates from the use of this technique to replace defective time code on a video tape recording by replacing it with a new time code sequence, which may be an extension of a previous good time code sequence on an earlier part of the source material.</text><links>
