<doc id="164597" wikidata="Q6803620" url="?curid=164597" title="Mean flow">
<text>In fluid dynamics, the fluid flow is often decomposed into a mean flow and deviations from the mean. The averaging can be done either in space or in time, or by ensemble averaging.

==Example==
Calculation of the mean flow may often be as simple as the mathematical mean: simply add up the given flow rates and then divide the final figure by the number of initial readings.

For example, given two discharges (&quot;Q&quot;) of 3 m³/s and 5 m³/s, we can use these flow rates &quot;Q&quot; to calculate the mean flow rate &quot;Q&quot;mean. Which in this case is &quot;Q&quot;mean = 4 m³/s.

==See also==
* Generalized Lagrangian mean

